The paper deals with image retrieval systems, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a flexible framework for supervised hashing, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of graph cuts, which is a common technique in computer vision and image processing (cs.IR, cs.MM). The use of boosted decision trees as hash functions is a machine learning technique (cs.AI).
